FT  13 SEP 94 / UK Company News: Amey more than trebled at Pounds 1.73m
Amey Holdings, the civil engineer which came to the market in June, reported
interim pre-tax profits more than trebled at Pounds 1.73m for the first half
of 1994.
This compared with Pounds 556,000 which included losses of Pounds 1.07m on
discontinued activities.
Profits on continuing activities rose by 6.8 per cent. Turnover was Pounds
97.3m, down from Pounds 109.4m which included Pounds 3.07m from discontinued
activities. The underlying fall was 8.5 per cent.
The company also confirmed that it was forming a joint venture with Taylor
Woodrow and Sir Robert McAlpine to tender for privately financed road
schemes.
The company said that the present six months had started well with trading
up on the comparable period.
Earnings per share were 4.8p (1.2p) and a dividend of 1.5p has been
declared.
